[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Extract SDOH mentions from a clinical note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this function would:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Call Comprehend Medical DetectEntitiesV2 for broad entity detection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Call a SageMaker endpoint hosting a fine-tuned SDOH NER model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Merge and deduplicate results from both passes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For this example, we use keyword matching with negation detection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to demonstrate the extraction structure. The output format matches
