[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text: The full text of the clinical note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Patient identifier for linking extractions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         encounter_date: ISO date string for temporal tracking.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of extraction dicts, each with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - domain: which SDOH category (housing, food, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - text_span: the matched text from the note
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - assertion: "AFFIRMED" or "NEGATED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - confidence: extraction confidence score (0-1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - patient_id: for downstream linkage
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - encounter_date: when this was documented
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     extractions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_lower = note_text.lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for domain, keywords in SDOH_KEYWORD_MAP.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for keyword in keywords:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if keyword in note_lower:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Found a mention. Now check for negation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Look at the 40 characters before the keyword for negation cues.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 keyword_pos = note_lower.index(keyword)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 prefix_window = note_lower[max(0, keyword_pos - 40):keyword_pos]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 is_negated = any(cue in prefix_window for cue in NEGATION_CUES)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 extractions.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "domain": domain,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "text_span": keyword,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "assertion": "NEGATED" if is_negated else "AFFIRMED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # Keyword matching gets lower confidence than a trained model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # A real NER model would output calibrated confidence scores.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "confidence": 0.65 if is_negated else 0.80,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "encounter_date": encounter_date,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Only take the first match per domain per note to avoid
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # double-counting when multiple keywords from the same domain appear.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 break
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return extractions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Feature Assembly
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `assemble_patient_features(patient_id, lookback_months)`. This step combines NLP extractions, structured screening data, and community indicators into a single feature vector per patient. The key design decision: distinguish "screened negative" from "never screened" by encoding missingness explicitly.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def assemble_patient_features(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     extractions: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     screening_data: Optional[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     community_data: Optional[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_count: int,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Build a unified feature vector for one patient from multiple data sources.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This combines:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - NLP-derived features (from clinical note extractions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Structured screening responses (if available)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Community-level indicators (if address is geocodable)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Derived features (burden score, documentation density)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The feature vector uses explicit NULL for missing data rather than
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     zero-filling. This matters because "no data" and "screened negative"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     are different signals for clustering.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Patient identifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         extractions: All SDOH extractions for this patient in the lookback window.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         screening_data: Dict of screening scores, or None if never screened.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         community_data: Dict of community indicators, or None if no address.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_count: Total clinical notes in the lookback window.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict of feature_name -> value (or None for missing).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     features = {"patient_id": patient_id}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- NLP-derived features (one set per SDOH domain) ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for domain in SDOH_DOMAINS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Filter to affirmed mentions in this domain.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         affirmed = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             e for e in extractions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if e["domain"] == domain and e["assertion"] == "AFFIRMED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         negated = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             e for e in extractions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if e["domain"] == domain and e["assertion"] == "NEGATED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Binary presence: was this domain ever mentioned as active?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features[f"{domain}_present"] = 1 if len(affirmed) > 0 else 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Mention frequency: more mentions suggest persistence or severity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features[f"{domain}_mention_count"] = len(affirmed)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Recency: days since most recent affirmed mention.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if affirmed:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             most_recent = max(e["encounter_date"] for e in affirmed)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             days_since = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 datetime.date.today()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 - datetime.date.fromisoformat(most_recent)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ).days
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             features[f"{domain}_days_since_last"] = days_since
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             features[f"{domain}_days_since_last"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Was this domain explicitly negated? (patient screened negative)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features[f"{domain}_negated"] = 1 if len(negated) > 0 else 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- Structured screening features ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if screening_data is not None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_completed"] = 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_food_score"] = screening_data.get("food_score")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_housing_score"] = screening_data.get("housing_score")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_transport_score"] = screening_data.get("transport_score")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_financial_score"] = screening_data.get("financial_score")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_social_score"] = screening_data.get("social_score")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_safety_score"] = screening_data.get("safety_score")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_completed"] = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_food_score"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_housing_score"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_transport_score"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_financial_score"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_social_score"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["screening_safety_score"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- Community-level features ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if community_data is not None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["adi_national_rank"] = community_data.get("adi_rank")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["food_desert_flag"] = community_data.get("food_desert")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["svi_overall"] = community_data.get("svi_overall")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["adi_national_rank"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["food_desert_flag"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         features["svi_overall"] = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- Derived features ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Total SDOH burden: count of domains with affirmed mentions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     features["sdoh_burden_count"] = sum(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         1 for d in SDOH_DOMAINS if features[f"{d}_present"] == 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Documentation density: how many notes does this patient have?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Low note counts mean NLP absence is less informative.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     features["note_count"] = note_count
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_mentions = sum(features[f"{d}_mention_count"] for d in SDOH_DOMAINS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     features["sdoh_mention_density"] = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_mentions / note_count if note_count > 0 else 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return features
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Gower Distance and Clustering
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `cluster_patients(feature_matrix, min_k, max_k)`. We compute Gower distance (which handles mixed binary, continuous, and missing features natively) and then apply hierarchical agglomerative clustering. The optimal cluster count is chosen by silhouette score.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import gower
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def prepare_feature_matrix(patient_features_list: list[dict]) -> pd.DataFrame:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Convert a list of patient feature dicts into a DataFrame suitable
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for Gower distance computation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Gower distance needs to know which columns are categorical (binary)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     vs. continuous. We encode that through pandas dtypes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Binary/categorical columns: kept as int or category
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Continuous columns: kept as float
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Missing values: kept as NaN (Gower handles these by excluding
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       the feature from that pair's distance calculation)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         DataFrame with one row per patient, columns are features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The patient_id column is dropped (not a clustering feature).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     df = pd.DataFrame(patient_features_list)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Store patient IDs separately; they're identifiers, not features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_ids = df["patient_id"].tolist()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     df = df.drop(columns=["patient_id"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convert None to NaN for proper missing-value handling.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     df = df.where(df.notna(), other=np.nan)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Ensure numeric types. Gower needs float for continuous columns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for col in df.columns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         df[col] = pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors="coerce")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return df, patient_ids
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def cluster_patients(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     feature_df: pd.DataFrame,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     min_k: int = MIN_CLUSTERS,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     max_k: int = MAX_CLUSTERS,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> tuple[np.ndarray, int, float]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Cluster patients using Gower distance + hierarchical agglomerative clustering.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Gower distance handles the mixed feature types in our matrix:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Binary features (domain_present): simple matching coefficient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Continuous features (ADI rank, SVI): range-normalized absolute difference
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Missing values: excluded from that pair's distance (computed over shared features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We try cluster counts from min_k to max_k and pick the one with the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     best silhouette score. Silhouette measures how well-separated clusters are:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     range -1 to 1, higher is better, above 0.25 is reasonable for social data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feature_df: DataFrame of patient features (no patient_id column).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         min_k: Minimum number of clusters to try.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         max_k: Maximum number of clusters to try.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Tuple of (cluster_labels, best_k, best_silhouette_score).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Compute the Gower distance matrix.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is the expensive step: O(n^2) pairwise comparisons.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # For 100K patients, you'd run this as a SageMaker Processing job.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Computing Gower distance matrix for %d patients", len(feature_df))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     distance_matrix = gower.gower_matrix(feature_df)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convert to condensed form for scipy's linkage function.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # scipy expects the upper triangle as a flat array.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     condensed_dist = squareform(distance_matrix, checks=False)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Hierarchical agglomerative clustering with Ward's linkage.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Ward's minimizes within-cluster variance, producing compact clusters.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Running hierarchical clustering (Ward's linkage)")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Z = linkage(condensed_dist, method="ward")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Try each candidate k and evaluate with silhouette score.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     best_k = min_k
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     best_score = -1.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     best_labels = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for k in range(min_k, max_k + 1):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         labels = fcluster(Z, t=k, criterion="maxclust")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Silhouette score needs at least 2 clusters and samples in each.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         n_unique = len(set(labels))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if n_unique < 2:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score = silhouette_score(distance_matrix, labels, metric="precomputed")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("  k=%d: silhouette=%.3f", k, score)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if score > best_score:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best_score = score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best_k = k
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best_labels = labels
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Best clustering: k=%d, silhouette=%.3f", best_k, best_score)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return best_labels, best_k, best_score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Phenotype Characterization and Equity Audit
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `characterize_phenotypes(feature_matrix, cluster_labels, patient_demographics)`. This step turns raw cluster IDs into interpretable phenotype profiles and checks for demographic overrepresentation that could enable discrimination.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def characterize_phenotypes(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     feature_df: pd.DataFrame,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     labels: np.ndarray,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_ids: list[str],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     demographics: dict[str, dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Characterize each cluster by its dominant SDOH features and run
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     an equity audit on demographic composition.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For each cluster, we compute:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Size (number of patients)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Prevalence of each SDOH domain (what % of cluster has this domain active)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Dominant domains (prevalence > 50%)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Average community indicators (ADI, SVI)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Demographic composition and overrepresentation flags
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The equity audit compares each cluster's racial composition to the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     overall population. If any group is overrepresented by more than 2x,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     we flag it. This doesn't mean the clustering is wrong, but it means
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     you need to examine why and ensure the phenotype is used to direct
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     resources, not to justify disparities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feature_df: The feature matrix used for clustering.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         labels: Cluster assignment for each patient (1-indexed from fcluster).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_ids: Patient IDs in the same order as feature_df rows.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         demographics: Dict of patient_id -> {"race": ..., "ethnicity": ...}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of phenotype profile dicts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Compute overall demographic distribution for comparison.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_races = [demographics.get(pid, {}).get("race", "Unknown") for pid in patient_ids]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     overall_race_dist = pd.Series(all_races).value_counts(normalize=True).to_dict()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     phenotypes = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     unique_labels = sorted(set(labels))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for cluster_id in unique_labels:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mask = labels == cluster_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cluster_df = feature_df[mask]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cluster_pids = [pid for pid, m in zip(patient_ids, mask) if m]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cluster_size = len(cluster_df)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Domain prevalence: what fraction of this cluster has each domain active?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         profile = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for domain in SDOH_DOMAINS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             col = f"{domain}_present"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if col in cluster_df.columns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 prevalence = cluster_df[col].mean()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 profile[domain] = round(prevalence, 3)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 profile[domain] = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Dominant domains: prevalence > 50% in this cluster.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         dominant = [d for d, p in profile.items() if p > 0.5]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Community indicator averages.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         avg_adi = cluster_df["adi_national_rank"].mean() if "adi_national_rank" in cluster_df else None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         avg_svi = cluster_df["svi_overall"].mean() if "svi_overall" in cluster_df else None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # --- Equity audit ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cluster_races = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             demographics.get(pid, {}).get("race", "Unknown") for pid in cluster_pids
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cluster_race_dist = pd.Series(cluster_races).value_counts(normalize=True).to_dict()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         equity_flags = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for race, cluster_pct in cluster_race_dist.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             overall_pct = overall_race_dist.get(race, 0.01)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ratio = cluster_pct / overall_pct if overall_pct > 0 else 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if ratio > 2.0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 equity_flags.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "race": race,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "cluster_pct": round(cluster_pct, 3),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "overall_pct": round(overall_pct, 3),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "overrepresentation_ratio": round(ratio, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phenotypes.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "cluster_id": int(cluster_id),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "size": cluster_size,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "domain_prevalence": profile,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "dominant_domains": dominant,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "avg_adi": round(float(avg_adi), 1) if avg_adi and not np.isnan(avg_adi) else None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "avg_svi": round(float(avg_svi), 3) if avg_svi and not np.isnan(avg_svi) else None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "equity_flags": equity_flags,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "name": None,  # Assigned by clinical team after review
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return phenotypes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Store Phenotype Assignments
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `store_phenotype_assignment(patient_id, phenotype, confidence, feature_snapshot)`. This writes each patient's phenotype to DynamoDB for real-time lookup by care management systems. Includes a staleness date so downstream systems know when to trigger re-evaluation.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_phenotype_assignment(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     phenotype: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     confidence: float,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model_version: str = "v1.0",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write a patient's phenotype assignment to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The record includes everything a care management system needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Which phenotype this patient belongs to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - How confident the assignment is
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - When it was assigned (for staleness tracking)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - When it expires (stale_after date)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - The model version that produced it (for reproducibility)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Patient identifier (partition key).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phenotype: The phenotype profile dict from characterize_phenotypes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         confidence: Membership confidence (0-1). For hard clustering this
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     is derived from distance to centroid; for soft clustering
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     it's the posterior probability.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model_version: Version string for the clustering model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The record that was written.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(PHENOTYPE_TABLE_NAME)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     now = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     stale_date = (now + datetime.timedelta(days=STALENESS_THRESHOLD_DAYS)).date()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "phenotype_id": phenotype["cluster_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "phenotype_name": phenotype.get("name") or f"Cluster {phenotype['cluster_id']}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "dominant_domains": phenotype["dominant_domains"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence": Decimal(str(round(confidence, 3))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "assigned_date": now.isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "stale_after": stale_date.isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "version": model_version,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled with synthetic data so you can see the end-to-end flow. In production, the data would come from your EHR extract, screening database, and geocoded community indicators. Here we generate synthetic patients to demonstrate the mechanics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import random
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def generate_synthetic_patients(n_patients: int = 200) -> tuple[list, list, dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Generate synthetic patient data for demonstration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Creates patients with varying SDOH profiles:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Some with housing + food issues (correlated, as they often are in reality)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Some with transportation barriers only
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Some with social isolation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Some with multi-domain complexity
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Many with no documented SDOH (the "low information" group)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Tuple of (patient_features_list, patient_ids, demographics_dict)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     random.seed(42)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     np.random.seed(42)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_features = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     demographics = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Define synthetic patient archetypes with probabilities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # These roughly mirror what you'd see in a real health system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     archetypes = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # (weight, domains_active, screening_available, community_deprived)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         (0.15, ["housing", "food", "financial"], True, True),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         (0.20, ["transportation"], False, False),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         (0.10, ["social_isolation", "safety"], True, True),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         (0.05, ["housing", "food", "transportation", "financial", "social_isolation"], True, True),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         (0.50, [], False, False),  # Low documentation / no SDOH signal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     races = ["White", "Black", "Hispanic", "Asian", "Other"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Intentionally skewed to test equity audit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     race_weights_by_archetype = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         [0.30, 0.35, 0.20, 0.10, 0.05],  # Housing+food: overrepresents Black
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         [0.50, 0.20, 0.15, 0.10, 0.05],  # Transport: roughly population
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         [0.60, 0.15, 0.10, 0.10, 0.05],  # Isolation: overrepresents White (elderly)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         [0.20, 0.40, 0.25, 0.10, 0.05],  # Multi-domain: overrepresents Black
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         [0.55, 0.20, 0.15, 0.07, 0.03],  # Low info: roughly population
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id_counter = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for arch_idx, (weight, domains, has_screening, is_deprived) in enumerate(archetypes):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         n_in_group = int(n_patients * weight)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for _ in range(n_in_group):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             patient_id_counter += 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             pid = f"PAT-{patient_id_counter:06d}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Generate synthetic note extractions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             extractions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for domain in SDOH_DOMAINS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if domain in domains:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # Active domain: generate 1-4 affirmed mentions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     n_mentions = random.randint(1, 4)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     for m in range(n_mentions):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         days_ago = random.randint(10, 300)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         enc_date = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             datetime.date.today() - datetime.timedelta(days=days_ago)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         ).isoformat()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         extractions.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "domain": domain,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "text_span": f"synthetic_{domain}_mention",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "assertion": "AFFIRMED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "confidence": random.uniform(0.7, 0.95),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "patient_id": pid,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "encounter_date": enc_date,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # Inactive domain: occasionally add a negated mention.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     if random.random() < 0.15:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         enc_date = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             datetime.date.today()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             - datetime.timedelta(days=random.randint(30, 400))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         ).isoformat()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         extractions.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "domain": domain,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "text_span": f"denies_{domain}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "assertion": "NEGATED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "confidence": 0.85,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "patient_id": pid,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             "encounter_date": enc_date,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Screening data (only for some patients).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             screening = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if has_screening and random.random() < 0.6:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 screening = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "food_score": random.randint(2, 8) if "food" in domains else random.randint(0, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "housing_score": random.randint(2, 8) if "housing" in domains else random.randint(0, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "transport_score": random.randint(2, 8) if "transportation" in domains else random.randint(0, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "financial_score": random.randint(2, 8) if "financial" in domains else random.randint(0, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "social_score": random.randint(2, 8) if "social_isolation" in domains else random.randint(0, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "safety_score": random.randint(2, 8) if "safety" in domains else random.randint(0, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Community indicators.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             community = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if random.random() < 0.8:  # 80% have geocodable addresses
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if is_deprived:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     community = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "adi_rank": random.randint(60, 99),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "food_desert": random.choice([0, 1]),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "svi_overall": round(random.uniform(0.6, 0.98), 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     community = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "adi_rank": random.randint(10, 55),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "food_desert": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "svi_overall": round(random.uniform(0.1, 0.45), 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Assemble features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             note_count = random.randint(3, 30)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             features = assemble_patient_features(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 patient_id=pid,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 extractions=extractions,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 screening_data=screening,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 community_data=community,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 note_count=note_count,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             patient_features.append(features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Demographics for equity audit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             race = random.choices(races, weights=race_weights_by_archetype[arch_idx])[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             demographics[pid] = {"race": race}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return patient_features, [f["patient_id"] for f in patient_features], demographics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_phenotyping_pipeline():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Execute the full SDOH phenotyping pipeline on synthetic data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This demonstrates the end-to-end flow:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Generate synthetic patient data (simulates NLP extraction + screening + community data)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Assemble feature matrix
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Cluster patients using Gower distance + hierarchical clustering
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Characterize phenotypes and run equity audit
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     5. Display results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, Step 1 would be replaced by actual Comprehend Medical calls,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     SageMaker endpoint invocations, Glue ETL jobs, and Location Service geocoding.
